<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
      Developer ID + Hardened Runtime entitlements for TFA.
      TFA is deliberately NOT sandboxed (it manages real tmux/ssh sessions and the user's files),
      so there are no App Sandbox keys here. Child processes it spawns (tmux, ssh, shells) run as
      separate processes and are not bound by this runtime, so no special "spawn" entitlement is
      needed. Everything is statically linked via SwiftPM (no external unsigned dylibs), so library
      validation stays ON. Kept minimal on purpose — add a key only if notarization/launch needs it.

      The point of Developer ID signing here is a STABLE signature: TCC grants (Desktop / Documents /
      "access other apps' data") then persist across launches and upgrades, instead of resetting every
      time as they did under ad-hoc signing.
    -->
</dict>
</plist>
